ent reports.</li><li>Establish dashboards and metrics for real-time performance monitoring.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>3. Commercial &amp; Strategic Partnering</strong></p><ul><li>Work closely with founders to evaluate new revenue streams, partnerships, and business models.</li><li>Lead commercial negotiations with suppliers, travel partners, technology vendors, and service providers.</li><li>Structure pricing models and revenue-sharing agreements that balance profitability and growth.</li><li>Provide strategic input on global expansion, market entry, and unit economics.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>4. Accounting, Reporting &amp; Taxation</strong></p><ul><li>Oversee <strong>day-to-day accounting</strong> operations, ensuring accuracy and adherence to IFRS/local GAAP.</li><li>Implement efficient bookkeeping processes and financial systems suitable for a startup scaling rapidly.</li><li>Prepare statutory accounts and management reports for internal and external stakeholders.</li><li>Manage <strong>direct and indirect taxation</strong> (VAT, corporate tax, withholding taxes) across multiple jurisdictions.</li><li>Liaise with auditors and tax consultants to ensure timely filings and compliance.</li><li>Monitor changes in accounting/tax regulations in UAE and other operating regions, ensuring proactive compliance.</li><li>Establish strong <strong>internal controls</strong> and policies to safeguard assets and prevent financial risks.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>5. Leadership &amp; Stakeholder Management</strong></p><ul><li>Act as a trusted partner to the founders and senior leadership team.</li><li>Mentor and grow a future finance team to support scaling.</li><li>Represent the company’s financial position to external stakeholders (banks, auditors, legal advisors).</li><li>Drive alignment between business objectives and financial sustainability.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>8–10 years of progressive finance experience, with at l