.</li><li>Collaborate with business and IT leaders to align data management with operational priorities and facilitate organizational change.</li><li>Architect end-to-end solutions for data management across enterprise applications and systems</li><li>Deliver reports, workshops, and presentations to internal and external stakeholders.</li><li>Provide thought leadership, training, and advice across projects and policies that impact data flows and governance.</li><li>Facilitate workshops and training sessions for data owners, stewards, and executives.</li><li>Act as a trusted advisor to business and technical stakeholders.</li><li>Define KPIs to measure the effectiveness of governance programs.<br><br></li></ul><strong>Required Skills and Requirements: <br><br></strong><ul><li>Minimum 5-10 years of work experience; most recent 5 years in data stewardship, data architecture and governance implementation. </li><li>A bachelor's degree in fields like computer science, information systems, business administration, or related disciplines</li><li>Excellent business writing, communication, and stakeholder management skills</li><li>Design &amp; Implementation experience with data management tools and technologies - catalog, marketplace, lineage, metadata management, quality, master data management, privacy &amp; security, observability, integration</li><li>Strong analytical and problem-solving skills</li><li>Ability to manage competing priorities and work collaboratively across business and IT teams</li><li>Consulting and stakeholder management skills to interface across technology and business functions</li><li>Up-to-date knowledge of cloud, hybrid, and modern data engineering patterns</li><li>The ability to adjust the level of technical detail, format, and frequency of communication based on the audience.<br><br></li></ul><em>We value diversity at our company. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sex