 diverse sales and marketing initiatives. Build and maintain relationships with associations, community leaders, NGOs, social media influencers, and other key stakeholders to promote LemFi’s services. Lead and manage a team of promoters to ensure effective market penetration and brand visibility. Drive awareness and trust within the Southeast Asian diaspora by engaging with communities and leveraging cultural touchpoints. Own and achieve customer acquisition and revenue targets in the designated sender country. Collaborate with internal teams to develop localized marketing campaigns and promotional activities tailored to the Southeast Asian audience. Monitor market trends, customer feedback, and competitor activity to optimize growth strategies. Act as a brand ambassador, ensuring that LemFi remains the preferred online remittance service for Southeast Asian migrants. RequirementsProven experience in sales, marketing, or community engagement, preferably within financial services, fintech, or diaspora-focused businesses. Strong network within Southeast Asian communities in the sender country. Ability to establish and nurture relationships with associations, NGOs, universities, and influencers. Experience leading teams, managing promoters, and executing grassroots marketing strategies. Strong communication, negotiation, and leadership skills. Data-driven mindset with the ability to track performance and optimize campaigns for growth. Ability to work independently in a fast-paced, target-driven environment.",
