nsultation with service owners.</li><li>Portfolio Monitoring: Monitor the solution portfolio to identify deficiencies, such as outdated technologies or misalignment with business requirements.</li><li>Lifecycle Accountability: Coordinate the technical lifecycle of the platform, informing service owners about the technology replacement roadmap and decisions.</li><li>End-of-Life Support: Aid product managers in decisions regarding the maintenance, refresh, or retirement of services, systems, and technologies.</li><li>Consultation and Design Alignment: Consult on infrastructure and application projects to ensure alignment with the overall architecture and modify designs as needed.</li><li>Architectural Design and Guidance: Create architectural designs to support product, service, and system development, ensuring alignment with enterprise architecture and project execution plans.</li></ul><li>We offer a permanent contract based on hybrid working mode.<br><br></li></ul><strong>About You<br></strong><ul><li>Bachelor degree or equivalent experience in computer science, information-technology, engineering, system analysis or a related study.</li><li>Relevant work experience of minimum five years in at least five IT solution development disciplines, including technical and infrastructure architecture, industrial architecture, operational technology, network management, application development, middleware, database management or cloud development, with exposure to multiple, diverse technologies, platforms and processing environments.</li><li>Competencies:</li><ul><li>Knowledge on:</li><li>Extensive expertise in integrating OT systems with IT networks while maintaining security and operational integrity. </li><li>Experienced in implementing security measures to ensure continuity, such as firewalls and intrusion detection systems, in compliance with standards like IEC 62443.</li><li>Expert in designing robust IoT infrastructure solutions to support seamless connectivity and dat