 Technology</li><li>Minimum 10 years of experience with cyber security, preferably in an Operational Technology (OT) environment.<br><br></li></ul><strong>Desired Characteristics<br><br></strong><ul><li>Demonstrated knowledge and understanding of the TCP/IP network stack, communication protocols and applications, including Modbus, DNP3, IEC61850, HTTPS, LDAP, RADIUS.</li><li>Demonstrated experience with Linux, VxWorks and Windows operating systems including user account management, security / system hardening, device control, and patch management.</li><li>Experience with Telecom and Network Equipment (Routers, Switches, Firewalls)</li><li>Experience with vulnerability assessment tools and penetration testing methodologies.</li><li>Knowledge of cyber asset protection regulations and standards affecting the utilities industry including NERC-CIP, NIST, IEC62443, IEC62351</li><li>Excellent oral and written communications skills</li><li>Ability to work effectively in a team and across functions, partnering with other teams in a worldwide environment</li><li>Cyber security certification (ex. ISC2, SANS, ISACA, GICSP)</li><li>Experience with programing and scripting languages.</li><li>Strong customer service mind-set</li><li>Strong interpersonal and leadership skills<br><br></li></ul>**For US Based Candidates**<br><br>The base pay range for this position is 158,000.00 - 210,600.00 USD Annual. The specific pay offered may be influenced by a variety of factors, including the candidate’s experience, education, and skill set. This position is also eligible for an 15% annual variable incentive bonus. This posting is expected to close on <em>10/3/25.<br><br></em><ul><li>The Company pays a geographic differential of 110%, 120% or 130% of salary in certain areas.<br><br></li></ul>Healthcare benefits include medical, dental, vision, and prescription drug coverage; access to a Health Coach, a 24/7 nurse-based resource; and access to the Employee Assistance Program, providing 24/7 co