reach strategies. </li><li>Pipeline Management: Maintain an accurate pipeline of prospects and manage lead data within Salesforce. </li><li>Educate &amp; Qualify: Share Halcyon’s value proposition and qualify leads for hand-off to Account Executives. </li><li>Nurturing: Consistently follow up with leads to ensure engagement until they are ready for deeper sales conversations. </li><li>Market Intelligence: Stay current on cybersecurity trends, compliance requirements, competitive landscape, and ransomware threats to communicate value effectively. <br><br></li></ul><strong>Requirements<br><br></strong><ul><li>1–3 years of experience in sales development or business development, preferably in cybersecurity or technology. </li><li>Business fluency in French and German (verbal and written) required. </li><li>Strong communication skills and ability to engage senior stakeholders. </li><li>Familiarity with CRM and sales engagement tools (Salesforce, Salesloft/Outreach, ZoomInfo, LinkedIn Navigator, Gong, etc.). </li><li>Proactive and able to thrive both independently and within a collaborative team. </li><li>Strong organisational skills with the ability to manage multiple priorities. </li><li>Proven track record of meeting or exceeding sales activity targets and KPIs. <br><br></li></ul><strong>Benefits<br><br></strong><ul><li>Comprehensive private healthcare (medical, dental) for employees and dependents (country-specific schemes apply). </li><li>Pension/retirement plan contributions aligned to local market standards. </li><li>Company-paid life and disability coverage (where applicable). </li><li>Flexible annual leave policy. </li><li>Paid parental leave. </li><li>Generous equity package. <br><br></li></ul><strong>Compensation<br><br></strong><ul><li>Base Salary Range: £40,000–£50,000 (or local currency equivalent) </li><li>Variable Commission: £15,000–£20,000 </li><li>On-Target Earnings (OTE): £55,000–£65,000 <br><br></li></ul>Actual compensation will vary based on experie