 hand-off to Account Executives. Nurturing: Consistently follow up with leads to ensure engagement until they are ready for deeper sales conversations. Market Intelligence: Stay current on cybersecurity trends, compliance requirements, competitive landscape, and ransomware threats to communicate value effectively. Requirements1–3 years of experience in sales development or business development, preferably in cybersecurity or technology. Business fluency in French and German (verbal and written) required. Strong communication skills and ability to engage senior stakeholders. Familiarity with CRM and sales engagement tools (Salesforce, Salesloft/Outreach, ZoomInfo, LinkedIn Navigator, Gong, etc.). Proactive and able to thrive both independently and within a collaborative team. Strong organisational skills with the ability to manage multiple priorities. Proven track record of meeting or exceeding sales activity targets and KPIs. BenefitsComprehensive private healthcare (medical, dental) for employees and dependents (country-specific schemes apply). Pension/retirement plan contributions aligned to local market standards. Company-paid life and disability coverage (where applicable). Flexible annual leave policy. Paid parental leave. Generous equity package. CompensationBase Salary Range: £40,000–£50,000 (or local currency equivalent) Variable Commission: £15,000–£20,000 On-Target Earnings (OTE): £55,000–£65,000 Actual compensation will vary based on experience, skills, and location. This role may also be eligible for equity in the Company.Diversity &amp; InclusionAt Halcyon, we know building resilience requires diverse perspectives. We are proud to be an equal opportunity employer and welcome applicants from all backgrounds.In accordance with applicable state and federal laws, the range provided is Halcyon’s reasonable estimate of the base compensation for this role. The actual amount may differ based on non-discriminatory factors such as experience, knowledge, skills, a