esting. </li><li>He will be responsible for mobilisation and follow up of the vendors.</li><li>He is responsible to ensure that the activities are done in line with commissioning schedule and according to established priorities.</li><li>Plan the commissioning tasks ensuring all commissioning requirements are captured in the Commissioning Database</li><li>He will have also to liaise with COMPANY representative and validate commissioning program for testing and energisation.</li><li>Coordinates commissioning punch list clearance activities with project team groups </li><li>Reports progress, performance, issues, and challenges to Commissioning Superintendent.<br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Experience and ideal profile: <br><br></strong><ul><li>Must have good experience in Oil &amp; Gas Industry in a similar or relevant position</li><li>Must have a recognised Technical XP in LV/HV distribution system testing, Electrical control systems, UPS and Battery testing, Relay testing, Turbo generator testing, ESDG and EDG testing, VFD/VSD equipment testing, </li><li>An experience in Hydrogen and electrolyser industry would be a Plus</li><li>Must have all the relevant trade accreditations required to perform the tasks required</li><li>Have experience in PTW and LOTO process.</li><li>A good command of English language is fundamental. <br><br><br></li></ul>We do not only offer you an opportunity, but also an inspiring experience in a truly international environment where you team up to push the boundaries through innovation, creativity and team spirit expressed by our people. Technip Energies attaches great importance work/life balance, values the human side and offers great flexibility in terms of work from home. In addition, we invite you to discover our ESG Roadmap which will allow you to have an overview of our current objectives and the values of our company: ESG Roadmap<br><br><strong>What’s next?<br><br></strong>Your profile will be seen and reviewed by our recruitment team an